The paper deals with the complexity of checking debates between a prover and a refuter about the membership of a string in a language, using limited space and randomness. This involves concepts from computational complexity theory (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT).
